Module jtamaro

Package jtamaro.data

package jtamaro.data
Purely functional data structures for Java.
  • Function* interfaces: object functions
  • Option: option monad
  • Pair: tuple with two elements
  • Triplet: tuple with three elements
  • Sequence: sequence of elements
  • Class
    Description
    Function0<R>
    A Function object that takes no argument.
    Function1<A,R>
    Function object that takes one argument.
    Function2<A,B,R>
    Function object that takes two arguments.
    Function3<A,B,C,R>
    Function object that takes three arguments.
    Function4<A,B,C,D,R>
    Function object that takes four arguments.
    Option<T>
    Option type is used to handle errors.
    Options
    Static methods for working with options.
    Pair<A,B>
    A tuple of two elements.
    Sequence<T>
    A Sequence is an ordered list of elements of type T, it corresponds directly to what you called "List-of-T" in PF1.
    Sequences
    Static methods for working with sequences.
    Triplet<A,B,C>
    A tuple of three elements.
